// ─── 3.1 Quick comparison ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
//  Playwright:
//    - Auto-waiting built in for actions/assertions.
//    - Modern APIs (frames, network mocking, tracing, video, etc.).
//    - Fast parallel execution and first-class test runner.
//
//  Selenium:
//    - Mature ecosystem and broad legacy support.
//    - Requires more explicit waits in many scenarios.
//    - Usually integrated with external runners/frameworks.
//
//  Rule of thumb:
//    Choose Playwright for new UI automation projects.
//    Choose Selenium if your organization depends on existing Selenium stack.


